Documentation REST API

HTTP Requests:
    - http://host/isuser/

        This request check telegramid in DB. You must select GET parameters.
        GET parameters:
            - idtelegram - Name Telegram user for checking.
            - SecretToken - Token your app. You can get it on admin.

        Answers:
            - 'Errors in get parameters' - it mean that you make error in name get paraneters.    
            - 'Errors' - it mean that token is not correct.
            - true - it mean that user is DB.
            - false - it mean that user isn't DB.
        Exemple:
            - http://127.0.0.1:8000/isuser/?SecretToken=1234&idtelegram=Serindgan



    - http://host/adduser/

        This request add user in DB. You must select GET parameters.
        GET parameters:
            - idtelegram - Name Telegram user.
            - name - Name user. 
            - surname - Surname user.
            - mobilenumber - Phone number user.
            - SecretToken - Token your app. You can get it on admin.

        Answers:
            - 'Errors in get parameters' - it mean that you make error in name get paraneters.    
            - 'Errors' - it mean that token is not correct.
            - 'True' - it mean that add complete.

        Exemple:
            - http://127.0.0.1:8000/adduser/?SecretToken=1234&idtelegram=Serindgan&name=Vay&surname=petrov&mobilenumber=87777

